ardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bricsummerthorne>BricSummerthorne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/28/03 1:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Laeyakk,<br>
<br>
Are you, or are you not, a Druid? I think you are not. The entire premise of this thread is misleading. &quot;Druids&quot; are not coming here asking for Wizard support, some dilettante thought it would be entertaining to play Devil's Advocate.<br>
<br>
Natan,<br>
<br>
If you believe that Clerics aren't boxed in by the design of the class, your understanding of balance is deeply flawed. Alternatively, you have terminal Green Grass syndrome, and should actually try playing one of the classes you see as perfect.<br>
<br>
Annoid,<br>
<br>
You've called Druids &quot;the most overpowered class in the game&quot;. In the Everquest I play, there is a class that can shut down 75% of a mob's damage output. There is a class that can heal fifteen thousand points of damage at a pop. There are classes that can turn monsters OFF. There are classes that can use multiple spell abilities on the run. There's a class that can slow, mez, nuke, heal, rez and FD. Druids are not those classes.<br>
<br>
I encourage you to clarify that &quot;most overpowered&quot; label, if in fact there is any reasoning behind it. <p>Bric ~ 59 Preserver ~ Fennin Ro<br>
